
[1]individually

   INDIVID'UALLY, adv. Separately; by itself; to the exclusion of others.
   Thirty men will unitedly accomplish what each of them individually
   cannot perform.

   1. With separate or distinct existence.

   How should that subsist solitarily by itself, which hath no substance,
   but individually the very same whereby others subsist with it?

   2. Inseparably; incommunicably.

   Omniscience--an attribute individually proper to the Godhead.
